## >>> Setup Goals

### Primary Use Cases
- **Gaming**: High-performance 1440p ultrawide gaming (main: 34" curved)
- **Content Creation**: Audio recording, streaming, video editing
- **Development**: Dual-boot Windows 11 + Arch Linux
- **Productivity**: Triple monitor workflow (ultrawide main + 1 side + 1 stacked above)

### Performance Targets
- **Gaming**: 120+ FPS @ 3440x1440 on high settings
- **Workstation**: Silent operation under load
- **Storage**: Fast boot times (<15s) for both OS

## /!\ Assembly Plan

### Phase 1: Core Build (Day 1)
#### Pre-Assembly Checklist
- [ ] Clear workspace (minimum 1m x 1m)
- [ ] Anti-static preparations
- [ ] Tools ready: Phillips screwdriver, cable ties
- [ ] Motherboard manual downloaded
- [ ] BIOS update USB prepared

#### Assembly Order
1. **Case Preparation**
   - [ ] Remove side panels from Lian Li LANCOOL 207
   - [ ] Install I/O shield
   - [ ] Pre-install standoffs (check case manual)
   - [ ] Route 24-pin and CPU power cables
   - [ ] Plan RGB/Digital display connections

2. **Motherboard Assembly (Outside Case)**
   - [ ] Install CPU (check AM5 orientation!)
   - [ ] Install RAM in slots 2 & 4 (A2/B2) - DDR5-6000
   - [ ] Install both M.2 SSDs with heatsinks
   - [ ] Pre-mount Arctic AIO pump block

3. **Case Installation**
   - [ ] Mount motherboard to LANCOOL 207
   - [ ] Install PSU (fan down if case has bottom filter)
   - [ ] Mount Arctic 360mm radiator (top exhaust recommended)
   - [ ] Install RTX 5060 Ti (check clearance)
   - [ ] Connect all power cables

4. **Initial Testing**
   - [ ] Power on test
   - [ ] POST check
   - [ ] Temperature monitoring

### Phase 2: Cooling & Cable Management (Day 1-2)
#### AIO Installation Details
- **Radiator Position**: Top-mounted, exhaust configuration
- **Pump Position**: CPU block orientation for best performance  
- **Fan Configuration**: Push/pull for maximum cooling
- **Cable Routing**: Clean path to CPU_FAN header

#### Cable Management
- [ ] 24-pin motherboard power
- [ ] 8-pin CPU power
- [ ] GPU power cables
- [ ] SATA power for any accessories
- [ ] Front panel connectors
- [ ] USB headers
- [ ] Audio headers

### Phase 3: Storage & OS Installation (Day 2)
#### Dual Boot Configuration
1. **Windows 11 Installation** (2TB Drive)
   - [ ] Create Windows installation media
   - [ ] Install on M.2 Slot 1
   - [ ] Windows updates
   - [ ] Driver installation
   - [ ] Gaming software setup

2. **Arch Linux Installation** (1TB Drive)
   - [ ] Arch installation media
   - [ ] Install on M.2 Slot 2
   - [ ] GRUB bootloader configuration
   - [ ] Development environment setup

## [>] Workspace Setup Plan

### Phase 4: Peripherals & Multi-Monitor Setup (Day 2-3)
#### Monitor Configuration
- [ ] **Primary Display**: Mount 34" ultrawide on Mozi Infinity Line arm
- [ ] **Secondary Display**: Position 1 existing monitor to the side using Basic Stand
- [ ] **Tertiary Display**: Stack 1 existing monitor above ultrawide (wall mount or stacked arm)
- [ ] **Cable Management**: Route all display cables behind desk
- [ ] **Display Settings**: 
  - Main: 3440x1440 @ 180Hz (gaming/primary work)
  - Side: Extended display for chat/monitoring
  - Top: Code/documentation/streaming tools
- [ ] **Gaming Profile**: HDR, adaptive sync setup for main display

#### Audio Production Setup
- [ ] Mount AT2020 microphone on Streamplify boom arm
- [ ] Connect XLR cable from mic to UMC22 interface
- [ ] USB connection from UMC22 to PC
- [ ] Position DT 990 Pro headphones for easy access
- [ ] **Software Configuration**:
  - Audio routing in Windows/Linux
  - Noise gate and EQ setup
  - Recording software (Reaper/Audacity)
  - Streaming software (OBS) audio setup

#### Workspace Ergonomics
- [ ] VARPELEV chair adjustment (height, lumbar, armrests)
- [ ] Monitor positioning (ultrawide centered, sides angled)
- [ ] Keyboard/mouse positioning relative to main display
- [ ] Microphone arm positioning (comfortable speaking distance)
- [ ] Lighting setup to reduce eye strain

## <=> Power & Thermal Management

### Power Distribution
- **Total System Power**: ~600W under full load
- **PSU Headroom**: 850W provides excellent efficiency curve
- **UPS Recommendation**: Consider 1000VA UPS for protection

### Cooling Strategy
- **Case Airflow**: Positive pressure setup
- **CPU**: 360mm AIO top exhaust
- **GPU**: Custom fan curves for quiet operation
- **Monitoring**: HWiNFO64, Core Temp

## ??? Testing & Validation

### Day 3: System Validation
#### Stability Testing
- [ ] CPU stress test (Prime95, 2+ hours)
- [ ] GPU stress test (FurMark, 1+ hour)  
- [ ] Memory test (MemTest86, overnight)
- [ ] Storage benchmark (CrystalDiskMark)
- [ ] Gaming stability test

#### Performance Benchmarks
- [ ] Cinebench R23 (CPU)
- [ ] 3DMark Time Spy (GPU)
- [ ] Game-specific benchmarks
- [ ] Boot time measurements

## {;} Software Configuration

### Windows 11 Setup
- [ ] NVIDIA/AMD drivers
- [ ] Motherboard chipset drivers
- [ ] Steam, Epic Games, etc.
- [ ] OBS Studio (streaming)
- [ ] Audio software (Reaper/Audacity)

### Arch Linux Setup
- [ ] Desktop environment (GNOME/KDE)
- [ ] Development tools
- [ ] Wine/Proton for gaming
- [ ] Audio production software

### Configuration  
- Update BIOS before OS installation
- Enable XMP/DOCP for RAM
- Set fan curves for noise optimization
- Regular thermal paste maintenance (yearly)

## /!\ Troubleshooting Quick Reference

| Issue | Check | Solution |
|-------|--------|----------|
| No POST | RAM seating, power connections | Reseat components |
| High temps | Fan operation, thermal paste | Check cooling |
| Boot issues | Boot priority, drive health | BIOS settings |
| Audio issues | Driver installation, connections | Update/reinstall |

